cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with wireless local area networks and the performance discrepancies between different nodes in the uplink, which are typical topics in the field of networked systems and communication. The use of cooperative protocols to mitigate these discrepancies is also a common research area in networking. Therefore, cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) and cs.IT (information theory) are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a new CSMA protocol, which falls under the category of cs.MA (multi-agent systems). The analysis of tradeoffs between throughput and energy expenses is related to optimization and control, which are covered by cs.SY (systems and control) and cs.MM (machine learning).
